##### Anything not starting with a @ is ignored


### Add the matrix files
@MATRIX petsc.matrices/1138_bus.pbin
@MATRIX petsc.matrices/spd-real-int32-float32

### Add a cg solver
@SOLVER cg 

### add a gmress solver with a parameter space. In this case, each call to a gmres solver will
# init 5 tests, one for each restart value.  
@SOLVER gmres 
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_restart 30 40 50 60 70
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_haptol 1e-30
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_preallocate FALSE
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_classicalgramschmidt none
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_cgs_refinement_type REFINE_NEVER
@PARAMETER -ksp_gmres_krylov_monitor FALSE

###minres solver with default parameters
@SOLVER minres 

### pipfcg with only one set of parameters  
@SOLVER pipefcg 
@PARAMETER -ksp_pipefcg_mmax 15   #  <15>: Number of search directions to storue (KSPPIPEFCGSetMmax) 
@PARAMETER -ksp_pipefcg_nprealloc 5   #  <5>: Number of directions to preallocate (KSPPIPEFCGSetNprealloc) 
@PARAMETER -ksp_pipefcg_truncation_type NOTAY   #  <NOTAY> (choose one of) STANDARD NOTAY (KSPFCGSetTruncationType) 

#### add a hypre boomeramg preconditioner with default parameters
@PRECON hypre boomeramg

#### block jacobi preconditioner with default parameters
@PRECON bjacobi


#####These are the solver-preconditioner pairs that will be tested. These follow all the
#####rules used by petsc for setting solvers and preconditioners. 

### The first one is cg preconditioned with boomeramg and block jacobi. This constitutes two tests,
#cg with boomer and cg with jacobi 
@PAIR cg boomeramg bjacobi

#### this one is 10 tests overall. 5 tests over the GMres parameter space with boomer and 5 with bjacobi
@PAIR gmres boomeramg bjacobi

@PAIR minres boomeramg bjacobi
@PAIR pipefcg boomeramg


